Job Posting Title:   SE_Simulation & Analysis Engineer_Expert
Description:

Deliver quality assured calculation models and results and propose where/when to perform specific simulation and analysis . Draw conclusions and make recommendations using control systems and function simulation and analyses. Perform analyses and deliver validated results with respect to design targets. Support continuous improvement of methods and tools. Act as technical expert for his/her discipline. Plan, lead and perform high complex simulations/analyses. Take responsibility for the fidelity of the simulations/analyses. Support project and design engineers in all stages of projects for technical solutions on varied complex level. Initiate and lead worldwide network. Drive innovation through collaboration with universities and external institutes or in-house developed tools. Make others engaged in innovation. Drive method and tool development globally. Train and mentor less experienced Simulation & Analysis Engineers globally. Provide input to Product and System Roadmaps. Perform project content evaluation and estimation in order to meet timeline and delivery. Perform method and tool development.

On Expert level the employee is a recognized expert in Simulation & Analysis Engineering typically obtained through advanced education and work experience.
- Experienced project lead and an established coach, mentor and educator to others in VG
- Known subject matter expert and a natural goto person for complex discipline related issues
- Strong Tshaped profile (either building deeper discipline excellence or developing mature generalist toolbox)
- Known product owner, often contributing to project roadmaps/strategies within context of industry trends
- Clear articulation of value creation by joining up the dots between their work and the TD/BA strategy.

Expert: position typically requires 10 years or more relevant experience

Volvo Group is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity in our workplace and we welcome all applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, gender or cultural background.

